Overview

Discover the allure of India's Golden Triangle tour, a captivating journey through Delhi, Agra, and Jaipur. Immerse yourself in the rich tapestry of history, culture, and architectural wonders as you explore iconic landmarks like the Taj Mahal, Red Fort, and Amber Fort. Experience the vibrant contrasts of modernity and tradition, spiritual sanctuaries, and bustling bazaars, all woven together to create an unforgettable travel experience.

Free cancellation: Cancel up to 24 hours in advance for a full refund

Pickup included: Pickup from airport, railway station, hotel or any other desired pickup location in Jaipur.

Bilingual Tour Guide: English, Hindi, Spanish, German, French

Wheelchair accessible: Available in most places

Book now & pay later: Just Call now at 8239902493 for booking or Additional arrangements.

Tour Plan

Day 1 Delhi

You will start your historical tour by Arriving at the airport on your own. We will pick you and make your Check-in at hotel, take your rest & breakfast.

Later visit Agrasen ki Baoli a famous step well. Overnight at Delhi.

Day 2 Delhi

Today we visit Raj Ghat & Red fort. We also drive past India Gate, Rashtrapati Bhavan and Parliament House, followed by a visit to Bahai Temple Lotus temple and Qutub Minar. Overnight in Delhi.

Sightseeing and shopping remain closed on Monday.

Day 3 Delhi To Agra

Today after breakfast continue your journey to the Historic City-Agra. Arrive at Agra and proceed to your hotel. Later half of the day we visit Taj Mahal and Agra Fort. Overnight at Agra

Note: Tickets to Taj Mahal are only available via online booking no manual tickets are available at present. Taj Mahal is closed on Friday.

Day 4 Agra To Jaipur

Today we continue our journey to the Pink city and capital of Rajasthan state Jaipur. On your way to Jaipur stop at Fatehpur Sikri which was the former capital of Emperor Akbar. Arrive at Jaipur and proceed to your hotel. Evening is at leisure. Overnight at Jaipur.

Day 5 Jaipur

Today we explore the city of Jaipur. Visit Hawa Mahal the palace of winds, Jantar Mantar A UNESCO World Heritage site also an astronomical marvel, and City Palace the royal residence, known for its architectural blend of Indian, Mughal, Rajput and European styles. Later we visit Panna Meena ka Kund and Amer Fort known for its Mughal influenced artistic style. In the evening witness a beautiful Sound & Light Show at Amer fort. Experience the city of Jaipur by night-driving past all illuminated monuments. Overnight stay in Jaipur.

Note: Sound & Light Show at Amer fort is subject operation.

Day 6 Jaipur To Hometown

After breakfast proceed to Jaipur Airport to board flight or Jaipur station to board your train to your hometown. Holiday Concludes. Lets stay in touch on Facebook\email and meet again on another memorable Holiday. See you soon!
